            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="35317996">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">第二章 由政体的性质直接引申出来的法律
第一节 三种政体(Governments)的性质(Nature)
1.	共和Republic: 全体人民或一部分人民握有最高权力(The body or only a part of the people is possessed of the supreme power)

2.	君主Monarchy: 一人执政，但依照固定的、确立的法律(a single person governs but by fixed established laws)

3.	专制 Despotic: 一人执政，依照自己的意志和性情(a single person directs everythi...</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2015-06-07 16:37</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                第二章 由政体的性质直接引申出来的法律<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>第一节 三种政体(Governments)的性质(Nature)<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>1.	共和Republic: 全体人民或一部分人民握有最高权力(The body or only a part of the people is possessed of the supreme power)<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>2.	君主Monarchy: 一人执政，但依照固定的、确立的法律(a single person governs but by fixed established laws)<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>3.	专制 Despotic: 一人执政，依照自己的意志和性情(a single person directs everything by his own will and caprice)<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>最初的基本法律(the first fundamental laws)：直接从政体的性质产生出来的<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>第二节 共和政体，与民主相关的法律(Of the Republican Government, and the Laws Relative to Democracy)<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>1.	Democracy: 全体人民(the body of the people)掌握最高权力<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>2.	民主政体里的人民既是君主(sovereign)，也是臣民(subject)<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>3.	只有通过选举(suffrage)，人民才能当君主。所以民主政体的基本法律是建立选举权利的法律(establish the right of suffrage)。要规定in what manner, by whom, to whom and concerning what, suffrages are to be given.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>4.	要规定组成议会(the public assemblies)的人数<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>5.	人民有最高权力，但对于那些无法做好的事情应交给代理人(ministers)去做。而代理人须由人民指派，这是民主政体的基本准则(a fundamental maxim)<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>6.	人民需要be directed by council(参政院) or senate(参议院). 人民选举产生<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>7.	人民有鉴别才德的能力，但不懂治理事务<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>8.	在平民政治下人民是分等级的(In a popular state the inhabitants are divided into certain classes).不应按照贵族政治的精神进行划分，变成资产与财富的选举，而应像梭伦那样按照民主的精神划分等级，让每个公民拥有选举权，规定被选举人而不是规定选举人。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>9.	选举用抽签(lot)进行<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>a)	Suffrage by lot is natural to democracy, as that by choice is to aristocracy.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>b)	It is a method of electing that offends no one; it lets each citizen entertain reasonable hopes of serving his country.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>c)	But it is naturally defective, needs regulations and amends.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>i.	军事职位用选择，参议员和法官用抽签Solon: military employments-by choice, senators and judges-by lot<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>ii.	要有很多花费的行政官用选择，其它用抽签Civil magistracies attended with great expense should be given by choice, and others by lot.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>iii.	抽签候选者需要为自荐None but those who presented themselves should be elected.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>iv.	抽中者由法官评判，所有人都有权利质疑The person elected should be examined by judges, everyone should have a right to accuse if he were unworthy of the office. This participated at the same time of the suffrage by lot, and of that by choice.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>v.	任期届满后需接受任期表现评价，这样能让没能力的人不自荐When the time of their magistracy was expired, they were obliged to submit to another judgement in regard to they were obliged to summit to another judgment in regard to the manner they had behaved. People who were utterly unqualified, must by this means have been extremely backward in giving in their names to be drawn by lot.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>10.	公开抽签<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>a)	公开抽签应是民主的基本法之一<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>b)	较低等的人可以被较高等的人指导，并受到某些人的庄严性的制约(restrained within bounds by the gravity of certain personages)<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>c)	不同于参议院(senate)和贵族团体(body of nobles)，密谋(intriguing)对于人民来说不危险，因为人民的本性是act through passion。当人们热衷金钱而不热衷国事，没有密谋才是共和国的不幸。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>11.	只有人民才有权力颁布法律(the people should have the sole power to enact laws)<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>a)	Yet there are a thousand occasions on which it is necessary the senate should have a power of decreeing.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>b)	正面例子：罗马和雅典，参议院可以颁布法律，试行一年，人民同意后才能perpetual
